import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns
from pybaseball import playerid_lookup, statcast_pitcher

# Fetch the player's ID
player_lookup = playerid_lookup('deGrom', 'Jacob')
degrom_id = player_lookup['key_mlbam'].values[0]

# Fetch the data
degrom_data = statcast_pitcher('2021-03-01', '2021-12-01', degrom_id)

# Inspect the structure of the fetched data
print(degrom_data.head())
print(degrom_data.columns)

# Clean and transform the data
degrom_cleaned_data = degrom_data.dropna(subset=['pfx_x', 'pfx_z'])
degrom_cleaned_data = degrom_cleaned_data[degrom_cleaned_data['game_type'] == 'R']
degrom_cleaned_data['pfx_x_in_pv'] = -12 * degrom_cleaned_data['pfx_x']
degrom_cleaned_data['pfx_z_in'] = 12 * degrom_cleaned_data['pfx_z']

# Make a named vector to scale pitch colors with
pitch_colors = {
    "4-Seam Fastball": "red",
    "2-Seam Fastball": "blue",
    "Sinker": "cyan",
    "Cutter": "violet",
    "Fastball": "black",
    "Curveball": "green",
    "Knuckle Curve": "purple",
    "Slider": "orange",
    "Changeup": "#7f7f7f",  # Replacing 'gray50' with its hexadecimal code
    "Split-Finger": "beige",
    "Knuckleball": "gold"
}

# Find unique pitch types to not have unnecessary pitches in legend
degrom_pitch_types = degrom_cleaned_data['pitch_name'].unique()

# Plot pitch movement
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 8))
sns.scatterplot(data=degrom_cleaned_data, x='pfx_x_in_pv', y='pfx_z_in', hue='pitch_name', palette=pitch_colors, alpha=0.25, s=60)
plt.axvline(0, color='gray', linewidth=1)
plt.axhline(0, color='gray', linewidth=1)
plt.xlim(-25, 25)
plt.ylim(-25, 25)
plt.gca().set_aspect('equal', adjustable='box')
plt.title('Jacob deGrom Pitch Movement\n2021 MLB Season | Pitcher\'s POV')
plt.xlabel('Horizontal Break (inches)')
plt.ylabel('Induced Vertical Break (inches)')
plt.legend(title='Pitch Name')
plt.show()

# Analyze velocity by inning
degrom_velo_by_inning = degrom_cleaned_data[degrom_cleaned_data['pitch_name'] == '4-Seam Fastball']
degrom_velo_by_inning = degrom_velo_by_inning.groupby(['inning', 'pitch_name']).agg(average_velo=('release_speed', 'mean')).reset_index()

# Plot velocity by inning
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
sns.lineplot(data=degrom_velo_by_inning, x='inning', y='average_velo', hue='pitch_name', marker='o', palette={'4-Seam Fastball': 'red'}, legend=False)
plt.ylim(90, 100)
plt.xticks(range(1, 10))
plt.title('Jacob deGrom 4-Seam Fastball Velo By Inning\n2021 MLB Season')
plt.xlabel('Inning')
plt.ylabel('Average Velo (mph)')
plt.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns
from pybaseball import playerid_lookup, statcast_pitcher

# Fetch the player's ID
player_lookup = playerid_lookup('deGrom', 'Jacob')
degrom_id = player_lookup['key_mlbam'].values[0]

# Define years to loop through
years = [2015, 2016, 2017, 2018, 2019]
all_data = []

for year in years:
    # Fetch the data for each year
    degrom_data = statcast_pitcher(f'{year}-03-01', f'{year}-12-01', degrom_id)
    
    # Clean and transform the data
    degrom_cleaned_data = degrom_data.dropna(subset=['pfx_x', 'pfx_z'])
    degrom_cleaned_data = degrom_cleaned_data[degrom_cleaned_data['game_type'] == 'R']
    degrom_cleaned_data['pfx_x_in_pv'] = -12 * degrom_cleaned_data['pfx_x']
    degrom_cleaned_data['pfx_z_in'] = 12 * degrom_cleaned_data['pfx_z']
    degrom_cleaned_data['year'] = year
    all_data.append(degrom_cleaned_data)
    
    # Create dynamic pitch colors
    unique_pitches = degrom_cleaned_data['pitch_name'].unique()
    pitch_colors = {
    "4-Seam Fastball": "red",
    "2-Seam Fastball": "blue",
    "Sinker": "cyan",
    "Cutter": "violet",
    "Fastball": "black",
    "Curveball": "green",
    "Knuckle Curve": "purple",
    "Slider": "orange",
    "Changeup": "#7f7f7f",  # Replacing 'gray50' with its hexadecimal code
    "Split-Finger": "beige",
    "Knuckleball": "gold",
    "Intentional Ball": "black",
    "Pitch Out": "brown"
    }
    
    # Plot pitch movement for each year
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 8))
    sns.scatterplot(data=degrom_cleaned_data, x='pfx_x_in_pv', y='pfx_z_in', hue='pitch_name', palette=pitch_colors, alpha=0.25, s=60)
    plt.axvline(0, color='gray', linewidth=1)
    plt.axhline(0, color='gray', linewidth=1)
    plt.xlim(-25, 25)
    plt.ylim(-25, 25)
    plt.gca().set_aspect('equal', adjustable='box')
    plt.title(f'Jacob deGrom Pitch Movement\n{year} MLB Season | Pitcher\'s POV')
    plt.xlabel('Horizontal Break (inches)')
    plt.ylabel('Induced Vertical Break (inches)')
    plt.legend(title='Pitch Name')
    plt.show()
    
    # Analyze velocity by inning for each year
    degrom_velo_by_inning = degrom_cleaned_data[degrom_cleaned_data['pitch_name'] == '4-Seam Fastball']
    degrom_velo_by_inning = degrom_velo_by_inning.groupby(['inning', 'pitch_name']).agg(average_velo=('release_speed', 'mean')).reset_index()
    
    # Plot velocity by inning for each year
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.lineplot(data=degrom_velo_by_inning, x='inning', y='average_velo', hue='pitch_name', marker='o', palette={'4-Seam Fastball': 'red'}, legend=False)
    plt.ylim(90, 100)
    plt.xticks(range(1, 10))
    plt.title(f'Jacob deGrom 4-Seam Fastball Velo By Inning\n{year} MLB Season')
    plt.xlabel('Inning')
    plt.ylabel('Average Velo (mph)')
    plt.show()

# Combine all years data
cumulative_data = pd.concat(all_data)

# Create dynamic pitch colors for cumulative data
unique_pitches_cumulative = cumulative_data['pitch_name'].unique()
pitch_colors_cumulative = {pitch: plt.cm.tab20(i / len(unique_pitches_cumulative)) for i, pitch in enumerate(unique_pitches_cumulative)}

# Plot cumulative pitch movement
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 8))
sns.scatterplot(data=cumulative_data, x='pfx_x_in_pv', y='pfx_z_in', hue='pitch_name', palette=pitch_colors_cumulative, alpha=0.25, s=60)
plt.axvline(0, color='gray', linewidth=1)

plt.gca().set_aspect('equal', adjustable='box')
plt.title('Jacob deGrom Pitch Movement\n2015-2019 MLB Seasons | Pitcher\'s POV')
plt.xlabel('Horizontal Break (inches)')
plt.ylabel('Induced Vertical Break (inches)')
plt.legend(title='Pitch Name')
plt.show()

# Analyze cumulative velocity by inning
cumulative_velo_by_inning = cumulative_data[cumulative_data['pitch_name'] == '4-Seam Fastball']
cumulative_velo_by_inning = cumulative_velo_by_inning.groupby(['inning', 'pitch_name']).agg(average_velo=('release_speed', 'mean')).reset_index()

# Plot cumulative velocity by inning
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
sns.lineplot(data=cumulative_velo_by_inning, x='inning', y='average_velo', hue='pitch_name', marker='o', palette={'4-Seam Fastball': 'red'}, legend=False)

import pandas as pd
from pybaseball import playerid_lookup, statcast_pitcher

# Fetch the player's ID
player_lookup = playerid_lookup('deGrom', 'Jacob')
degrom_id = player_lookup['key_mlbam'].values[0]

# Define years to loop through
years = [2015, 2016, 2017, 2018, 2019]
all_data = []

# Initialize an empty DataFrame to store cumulative results
cumulative_pitch_counts = pd.DataFrame()

for year in years:
    # Fetch the data for each year
    degrom_data = statcast_pitcher(f'{year}-03-01', f'{year}-12-01', degrom_id)
    
    # Clean and transform the data
    degrom_cleaned_data = degrom_data.dropna(subset=['pitch_name', 'type'])
    
    # Calculate ball and strike counts per pitch type
    pitch_counts = degrom_cleaned_data.groupby(['pitch_name', 'type']).size().unstack(fill_value=0)
    pitch_counts['Total Count'] = pitch_counts.sum(axis=1)
    pitch_counts['Bad Ball Ratio'] = (pitch_counts['B'] + pitch_counts['X']) / pitch_counts['Total Count']
    pitch_counts['Strike Ratio'] = pitch_counts['S'] / pitch_counts['Total Count']
    pitch_counts.reset_index(inplace=True)
    
    # Rename columns for clarity
    pitch_counts.columns.name = None
    pitch_counts.rename(columns={'B': 'Ball Count', 'S': 'Strike Count'}, inplace=True)
    
    # Add year information
    pitch_counts['Year'] = year
    all_data.append(pitch_counts)
    
    # Display the DataFrame for the current year
    print(f"Ball and Strike Ratio for {year}")
    print(pitch_counts)
    print("\n")
    
    # Append to cumulative results using pd.concat
    cumulative_pitch_counts = pd.concat([cumulative_pitch_counts, pitch_counts], ignore_index=True)

# Cumulative analysis
cumulative_counts = cumulative_pitch_counts.groupby(['pitch_name']).sum()
cumulative_counts['Bad Ball Ratio'] = (cumulative_counts['Ball Count'] + cumulative_counts['X']) / cumulative_counts['Total Count']
cumulative_counts['Strike Ratio'] = cumulative_counts['Strike Count'] / cumulative_counts['Total Count']
cumulative_counts.reset_index(inplace=True)

# Display the cumulative DataFrame
print("Cumulative Ball and Strike Ratio from 2015 to 2019")
print(cumulative_counts)

import pandas as pd
from pybaseball import playerid_lookup, statcast_pitcher

# Fetch the player's ID
player_lookup = playerid_lookup('deGrom', 'Jacob')
degrom_id = player_lookup['key_mlbam'].values[0]

# Define years to loop through
years = [2015, 2016, 2017, 2018, 2019]
overall_ratios = []

for year in years:
    # Fetch the data for each year
    degrom_data = statcast_pitcher(f'{year}-03-01', f'{year}-12-01', degrom_id)
    
    # Clean and transform the data
    degrom_cleaned_data = degrom_data.dropna(subset=['type'])
    
    # Calculate ball and strike counts
    total_counts = degrom_cleaned_data['type'].value_counts()
    bad_ball_count = total_counts.get('B', 0) + total_counts.get('X', 0)
    strike_count = total_counts.get('S', 0)
    total_count = bad_ball_count + strike_count
    
    # Calculate ball and strike ratios
    bad_ball_ratio = bad_ball_count / total_count if total_count != 0 else 0
    strike_ratio = strike_count / total_count if total_count != 0 else 0
    
    # Append the results to the list
    overall_ratios.append({
        'Year': year,
        'Bad Ball Ratio': bad_ball_ratio,
        'Strike Ratio': strike_ratio
    })

# Create a DataFrame from the results
overall_ratios_df = pd.DataFrame(overall_ratios)

# Display the DataFrame
print("Overall Bad Ball and Strike Ratios by Year")
print(overall_ratios_df)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from pybaseball import playerid_lookup, statcast_pitcher

# Fetch the player's ID
player_lookup = playerid_lookup('deGrom', 'Jacob')
degrom_id = player_lookup['key_mlbam'].values[0]

# Define the period to fetch data
start_date = '2015-01-01'
end_date = '2019-12-31'

# Fetch the data for the specified period
degrom_data = statcast_pitcher(start_date, end_date, degrom_id)

# Clean and transform the data
degrom_cleaned_data = degrom_data.dropna(subset=['pfx_x', 'pfx_z'])
degrom_cleaned_data = degrom_cleaned_data[degrom_cleaned_data['game_type'] == 'R']
degrom_cleaned_data['pfx_x_in_pv'] = -12 * degrom_cleaned_data['pfx_x']
degrom_cleaned_data['pfx_z_in'] = 12 * degrom_cleaned_data['pfx_z']

# Filter for strikes
strike_data = degrom_cleaned_data[degrom_cleaned_data['type'] == 'S']

# Calculate the mean coordinates for each pitch type using pfx_x and pfx_z
mean_coordinates = strike_data.groupby('pitch_name')[['pfx_x_in_pv', 'pfx_z_in']].mean().reset_index()

# Rename columns for clarity
mean_coordinates.rename(columns={'pfx_x_in_pv': 'Mean_pfx_x_in_pv', 'pfx_z_in': 'Mean_pfx_z_in'}, inplace=True)

# Display the DataFrame
print("Best Coordinates for Each Pitch Type Resulting in a Strike")
print(mean_coordinates)

# Plot the mean coordinates
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
for index, row in mean_coordinates.iterrows():
    plt.scatter(row['Mean_pfx_x_in_pv'], row['Mean_pfx_z_in'], label=row['pitch_name'], s=100)  # s is the size of the markers

plt.axvline(0, color='gray', linewidth=1)
plt.axhline(0, color='gray', linewidth=1)
plt.xlim(-25, 25)
plt.ylim(-25, 25)
plt.title('Mean Coordinates for Each Pitch Type Resulting in a Strike\nJacob deGrom (2015-2019)')
plt.xlabel('Horizontal Break (inches)')
plt.ylabel('Induced Vertical Break (inches)')
plt.legend(title='Pitch Type')
plt.show()
